---
import SiteLayout from '../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "BBQ Sauce Recipes from Scratch",
    "description": "Learn how to make 8 regional BBQ sauce recipes from scratch: Kansas City, Carolina mustard, Eastern NC vinegar, Alabama white, Texas mop, Memphis dry rub, Korean gochujang, and honey chipotle.",
    "url": "https://28grams.vip/bbq-sauce-recipes",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "28grams"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long does homemade BBQ sauce last in the fridge?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most homemade BBQ sauces will last 1 to 2 weeks in an airtight container in the refrigerator. Vinegar-heavy sauces may last up to a month."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can I freeze homemade BBQ sauce?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes, you can freeze BBQ sauce for up to 3 months. Leave some room in the container for expansion as it freezes."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why is my BBQ sauce too thin?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "If your sauce is too thin, simmer it uncovered for longer to reduce and thicken, or whisk in a cornstarch slurry (1 part cornstarch to 1 part water)."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When should I apply BBQ sauce to meat?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Apply sweet and thick BBQ sauces during the last 15-20 minutes of cooking to prevent the sugars from burning and turning bitter."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Are Memphis dry rubs considered BBQ sauce?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "While not a liquid sauce, Memphis dry rubs are an essential flavoring component applied directly to the meat before or after smoking, functioning similarly to a sauce in flavor delivery."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];

const mainEntityArray = schema[1].mainEntity;
---

<SiteLayout
  site="28grams"
  title="BBQ Sauce Recipes from Scratch"
  description="Learn how to make 8 regional BBQ sauce recipes from scratch: Kansas City, Carolina mustard, Eastern NC vinegar, Alabama white, Texas mop, Memphis dry rub, Korean gochujang, and honey chipotle."
  canonical="https://28grams.vip/bbq-sauce-recipes"
  schema={JSON.stringify(schema)}
>
  <style>
* { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
.page-wrapper {
  font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
  background: #0a060a;
  color: #e0d0d8;
  min-height: 100vh;
  --card-bg: #120c10;
  --border-color: #2a1820;
  --accent-color: #C2185B;
  --text-secondary: #888;
}

code, .mono { font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

.hero { text-align: center; padding: 48px 24px 24px; background: linear-gradient(180deg, #1a0a14 0%, #0a060a 100%); }
.hero h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; font-weight: 900; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 6px; }
.hero h1 span { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent-color), #ff6b9d); -webkit-background-clip: text; -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent; background-clip: text; }
.hero p { color: #666; font-size: 0.95rem; max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; }
.main { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 32px 20px 40px; }

.formula-card, .guide-card {
  background: var(--card-bg);
  border: 2px solid var(--border-color);
  border-radius: 16px;
  overflow: hidden;
  margin-bottom: 32px;
}
.card-header {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 16px 20px;
  background: #150d12;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}
.card-header h2 { font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin: 0; }
.card-content { padding: 20px; }
.card-content p { color: #c8b8c0; line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.card-content ul { padding-left: 20px; margin-bottom: 12px; color: #c8b8c0; line-height: 1.6; }
.card-content li { margin-bottom: 6px; }

.content p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: #777; line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 14px; }

.recipe-section { margin-bottom: 40px; padding-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
.recipe-section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }
.recipe-header { display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.recipe-header h3 { margin: 0; font-size: 1.3rem; color: var(--accent-color); }
.recipe-meta { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-secondary); background: #1a1015; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }

.recipe-info-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
}
.recipe-info-card {
    background: #150d12;
    padding: 12px 16px;
    border-radius: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
}
.recipe-info-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.recipe-info-value {
    color: #e0d0d8;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
}

.faq-list { margin-top: 24px; }
.faq-item { margin-bottom: 24px; }
.faq-q { font-weight: 700; color: #fff; margin-bottom: 8px; font-size: 1.05rem; }
.faq-a { color: #777; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.6; }

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .hero h1 { font-size: 1.8rem; }
  .recipe-header { flex-direction: column; gap: 4px; }
}
  </style>

<div class="page-wrapper">
<div class="hero">
  <h1>BBQ Sauce <span>Recipes</span> 🍖</h1>
  <p>8 regional BBQ sauce recipes from scratch: Kansas City, Carolina mustard, Eastern NC vinegar, Alabama white, Texas mop, Memphis dry rub, Korean gochujang, and honey chipotle.</p>
</div>

<div class="main">
  <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 40px 0 20px;">The Recipes</h2>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>1. Kansas City Classic</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Tomato & Molasses</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Ketchup, brown sugar, molasses, apple cider vinegar, spices.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Simmer all ingredients 20 mins.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Ribs, burnt ends, chicken.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">2 weeks in fridge.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>2. Carolina Gold</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Mustard-Based</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Yellow mustard, honey, apple cider vinegar, brown sugar, black pepper.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Whisk until smooth, do not boil.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Pulled pork, sausages.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">3 weeks in fridge.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>3. Eastern NC Vinegar</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Vinegar & Pepper</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Apple cider vinegar, red pepper flakes, black pepper, salt, touch of brown sugar.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Shake well and steep overnight.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Whole hog, pulled pork.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Months at room temp.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>4. Alabama White Sauce</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Mayo-Based</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Mayonnaise, apple cider vinegar, lemon juice, black pepper, horseradish.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Whisk until thin and creamy.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Smoked chicken.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">1 week in fridge.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>5. Texas Mop Sauce</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Thin Basting Liquid</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Beef broth, vinegar, Worcestershire, oil, spices.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Warm up to blend flavors.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Brisket basting during smoke.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Discard after raw meat contact.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>6. Memphis Dry Rub</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Spice Blend</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Paprika, brown sugar, black pepper, garlic powder, onion powder, celery seed.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Mix thoroughly. Apply heavy.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Pork ribs.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">6 months in pantry.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>7. Korean Gochujang BBQ</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Spicy & Sweet</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Gochujang paste, soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar, garlic, ginger.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Whisk until smooth paste.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Pork belly, short ribs (Galbi).</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">2 weeks in fridge.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="recipe-section">
    <div class="recipe-header"><h3>8. Honey Chipotle</h3><span class="recipe-meta">Sweet & Smoky Heat</span></div>
    <div class="recipe-info-grid">
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Ingredients</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Chipotles in adobo, honey, ketchup, apple cider vinegar, cumin.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Method</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Blend until smooth, simmer 10 mins.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Usage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">Wings, chicken thighs.</div></div>
      <div class="recipe-info-card"><div class="recipe-info-label">Storage</div><div class="recipe-info-value">2 weeks in fridge.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 40px 0 20px;">Sauce Science</h2>

  <div class="formula-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>Sugar Caramelization</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Sugars in sauces (like brown sugar or molasses) caramelize beautifully on meat, creating a desirable bark and complex flavor. However, they can easily burn if exposed to high heat for too long. This is why thick, sweet sauces like Kansas City style should be applied during the final 15-20 minutes of cooking rather than as a marinade.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="formula-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>Vinegar Tenderizing</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Acids like apple cider vinegar, common in Carolina and Eastern NC sauces, serve dual purposes. They cut through the rich, fatty mouthfeel of pulled pork or brisket, balancing the flavor profile. Furthermore, applying vinegar-based mop sauces during the cooking process can subtly break down surface proteins, contributing to a more tender exterior bark.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="formula-card">
    <div class="card-header">
      <h2>Emulsification</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="card-content">
      <p>Sauces like Alabama White rely on mayonnaise, which is an emulsion of oil and egg yolk. When whisked with vinegar and lemon juice, the sauce becomes thin enough to drizzle or dip while maintaining its creamy, cohesive texture. Proper emulsification ensures the sauce coats the meat evenly without separating into oily layers.</p>
    </div>
  </div>


  <h2 style="font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 800; color: #fff; margin: 40px 0 20px;">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
  <div class="faq-list">
    {mainEntityArray.map((faq) => (
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">{faq.name}</div>
        <div class="faq-a">{faq.acceptedAnswer.text}</div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
</div>
</div>
</SiteLayout>